cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.DC 

This paper discusses a software switch used in Software-Defined Networking (SDN), which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the architecture and evaluation of the switch, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper mentions modifications and customization of the switch, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
